
[1]vestal

   VEST'AL, a. [L. vestalis, from Vesta, the goddess of fire, Gr.]

   1. Pertaining to Vesta, the goddess of fire among the Romans, and a
   virgin.

   2. Pure; chaste.

      VEST'AL, n. A virgin consecrated to Vesta, and to the service of
   watching the sacred fire, which was to be perpetually kept burning upon
      her altar. The Vestals were six in number, and they made a vow of
                            perpetual virginity.
